    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your chicken out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Chop your<strong> tomato[es]</strong> in half</p><p>Cut a piece of <strong>tin foil</strong> approx. the size of an A4 sheet of paper and add half of the <strong>tomato[es] </strong>(save the rest for later!) to the foil</p><p>Chop the <strong>remaining tomato halves</strong> into wedges</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/herby-chicken-salad-with-tomato-dressing-and-cheesy-croutons/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> balsamic vinegar </strong>and<strong> tomato paste</strong> to the foil and scrunch the foil around the <strong>tomato</strong> to form a tightly sealed parcel</p><p>Add the <strong>tomato parcel</strong> to one side of a baking tray</p><p>Tear your<strong> ciabatta[s]</strong> into bite-sized pieces and add to the other side of the baking tray with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? Use 2 trays!</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/herby-chicken-salad-with-tomato-dressing-and-cheesy-croutons/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Sprinkle <strong>most</strong> of your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> (save the rest for garnish!) over the torn ciabatta</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 7-8 min or until the ciabatta is golden and crispy and the tomato is softened \u2013 these are your <strong>cheesy croutons & roasted tomato</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/herby-chicken-salad-with-tomato-dressing-and-cheesy-croutons/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, slice through the thickest part of your <strong>chicken breast portion[s] </strong>being careful not to cut all the way through to the other side and open it out like a book</p><p>Cover with <strong>cling film</strong> and bash them with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> until evenly flattened and approx. 1cm in thickness</p><p>Season the flattened chicken with your <strong>dried basil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> seasoned chicken</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/herby-chicken-salad-with-tomato-dressing-and-cheesy-croutons/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil </strong>on a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>seasoned chicken</strong> and cook for 4 min on each side until golden, then turn the heat down to medium and cook for a further 3-4 min or until cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>herby chicken</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? You may need to do this in 2 batches!</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/herby-chicken-salad-with-tomato-dressing-and-cheesy-croutons/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, wash your<strong> salad</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/herby-chicken-salad-with-tomato-dressing-and-cheesy-croutons/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the croutons are golden and crisp, remove the tray[s] from the oven</p><p>Transfer the<strong> roasted tomato</strong> to a bowl<strong> </strong>(careful, this will be hot!)</p><p>Add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]<strong> </strong></span><strong>olive oil </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>to the bowl with 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span><strong> sugar </strong>and mash everything together with a fork \u2013 this is your <strong>tomato dressing</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/herby-chicken-salad-with-tomato-dressing-and-cheesy-croutons/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>To serve, layer the <strong>salad</strong>, <strong>tomato wedges</strong> and the <strong>cheesy croutons</strong>, then drizzle over the<strong> tomato dressing</strong></p><p>Slice the <strong>herby chicken</strong> and serve it on top</p><p>Sprinkle over the<strong> remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
